<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id4cfdb596-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s12252"><num value="12252">§ 12252.</num><heading> Eligibility to receive grants</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">To be eligible to receive a grant under <ref href="/us/usc/t34/s12251">section 12251 of this title</ref>, a State shall submit to the Attorney General an application at such time, in such form, and containing such information as the Attorney General reasonably may require by rule.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id4cfdb597-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/322/tIII/s31912">Pub. L. 103–322, title III, § 31912</ref>, <date date="1994-09-13">Sept. 13, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/1895">108 Stat. 1895</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id4cfdb598-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id4cfdb599-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id4cfdb59a-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s13892">section 13892 of Title 42</ref>, The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.</p>
</note>
</notes>
